I literally threw this together from what I had in the house a couple days before payday, so I had to do some substitutions. I had no celery and no marjoram and I had russets instead of boiling potatoes. I substituted thyme for the tarragon, left out the celery and used the potatoes I had. I use olive oil for my "fat of choice" whenever possible, so I sauted the veggies in olive oil, not butter. I also used a heart-healthy margarine in the roux instead of butter. If I had any issues at all with the recipe, it's in the instructions for the roux. Cook a glob of flour smoothly blended into the margarine for 3 minutes while whisking? I gave up after 2 minutes of nothing happening and all the roux inside the balloon of the whisk. Dear hubby liked this recipe. The quantity made is generous and he has leftovers for lunch. When I asked if I should make it again, I got an enthusiastic yes.

