Rating: 3
I used this recipe and referenced another from this site, "Leek, Potato, and Sausage Soup," as well. If you wish to cut the butter in this recipe, just don't do so with the roux, which requires a balance of fat to starch. Taking the time to let the stock reduce was key, I think. We used hot Italian sausage, rolled into tiny balls and browned, as per several previous reviewers. I think next time, I'd cook the potatoes separately -- and account for the liquid they soak up by letting the mixture reduce further -- then puree them before adding to the stock, for a creamier soup (without requiring more butter).

