I'm going to be one of those annoying reviewers who rate a recipe and proceed to describe all the changes I made to it. I did enjoy the soup, oiliness and all, even though I cut the butter back. Although I did add a little olive oil in with the butter while sautéeing the carrots and celery. Incidentally, I tripled the amount of carrots and celery. I also sautéed the double the amount of sausages (of which I used spicy Italian), which I think is better than just throwing meat in a pot of boiling liquid. It gives the soup extra flavour. I set it aside and then threw it in during the last ten minutes of cooking. Instead of using marjoram, I used dry thyme and oregano, and put the potatoes in earlier than the recipe specified so that it would cook through properly. I was disappointed to find the soup was not as thick as i had anticipated. Perhaps it is because I left the pot covered or partially so for some of the boiling and simmering time, which created more steam and hence more liquid. All of this to say this is a good, basic starter recipe. It stands to see improvements, but is a good basis for creativity and embellishments.

